5|$|Martin Luther King Jr. was the {{conscience}} of his generation. He gazed upon <b>the</b> <b>great</b> <b>wall</b> <b>of</b> segregation {{and saw that the}} power of love could bring it down. From the pain and exhaustion of his fight to fulfill the promises of our founding fathers for our humblest citizens, he wrung his eloquent statement of his dream for America. He made our nation stronger because he made it better. His dream sustains us yet.|$|E
